# bootaa64.efi provenance

Vendored ROCKNIX GRUB binary, extracted verbatim from the FAT partition
(EFI/BOOT/bootaa64.efi) of the official release image:

  release:  https://github.com/ROCKNIX/distribution/releases/tag/20260701
  asset:    ROCKNIX-SM8250.aarch64-20260701.img.gz
  img.gz sha256: c4bd6943abe46b438b97d66060b02b8b4a9169c99972b3c8cbcfba94a8228df0
  bootaa64.efi sha256: d6d0939dce9462f8ad675e4f26d833f3833e0e0a2461a2d4e7b5e25247801675

It is GRUB 2.14-rc1 built by ROCKNIX (GPL-3.0-or-later; source: ROCKNIX
distribution repo, packages/tools/grub: package.mk + 5 patches, notably
grub-silent-boot, framebuffer rotation, and the partfind/strsearch rawsearch
commands their board-autodetect grub.cfg uses). Vendored rather than
self-built so the SM8250 boot chain uses the exact binary ROCKNIX ships and
tests against the same ABL. To self-build instead: ALARM's grub +
grub-mkimage -O arm64-efi -p /boot/grub with ROCKNIX's module list (their
package.mk makeinstall_target), plus their patches if the autodetect cfg
commands are wanted.

grubenv is the pristine environment block from the same image. grubenv on
/flash is user state (saved menu choice) — never overwritten on upgrade.

grub.cfg.rocknix-reference is the GENERATED grub.cfg from the same image
(boot=LABEL LibreELEC-style cmdline, savedefault menu, one entry per board) —
kept as the reference for porting the multi-board menu/autodetect when a
second sm8250 board lands. Our shipped grub.cfg is the pocknix-authored
static one (root=PARTLABEL, single rp5 entry, timeout 0).
